Sentencas: Samarium doped ceria (SDC) shows obvious electronic conduction in a reducing atmosphere, which results in internal short-circuiting of the SOFC.
Titulo: Linear discharge model, power losses and overall efficiency of the solid oxide fuel cell with thin film samarium doped ceria electrolyte. Part II: Power losses and overall efficiency

Sentencas: In this work, we initiatively combine the Gorelov modified electromotive force (EMF) method and the Liu modified EMF method to determine the internal electronic resistance of the SOFC with 60 mu m SDC film electrolyte.
Titulo: Linear discharge model, power losses and overall efficiency of the solid oxide fuel cell with thin film samarium doped ceria electrolyte. Part II: Power losses and overall efficiency

Sentencas: The internal electronic resistance determined with the Gorelov modified EMF method is a little larger than that determined with the Liu modified EMF method.
Titulo: Linear discharge model, power losses and overall efficiency of the solid oxide fuel cell with thin film samarium doped ceria electrolyte. Part II: Power losses and overall efficiency

Sentencas: The power loss of the SOFC is mainly resulted from the internal short-circuiting, oxygen ionic resistance and electrode polarization resistance.
Titulo: Linear discharge model, power losses and overall efficiency of the solid oxide fuel cell with thin film samarium doped ceria electrolyte. Part II: Power losses and overall efficiency

Sentencas: At low external current density, the internal short-circuiting power loss is predominant, while at high current density the oxygen ionic resistance power loss is predominant.
Titulo: Linear discharge model, power losses and overall efficiency of the solid oxide fuel cell with thin film samarium doped ceria electrolyte. Part II: Power losses and overall efficiency

Sentencas: Temperature has little effect on the maximum efficiency of the SOFC.
Titulo: Linear discharge model, power losses and overall efficiency of the solid oxide fuel cell with thin film samarium doped ceria electrolyte. Part II: Power losses and overall efficiency

Sentencas: When the SOFC works at the maximum power output, the efficiency of the cell is about 30%, but if the electronic conduction of the SDC electrolyte could be eliminated, the efficiency could be improved by 2.5 times.
Titulo: Linear discharge model, power losses and overall efficiency of the solid oxide fuel cell with thin film samarium doped ceria electrolyte. Part II: Power losses and overall efficiency
